<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41021f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41021f">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41021f"> 21(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> divorced wife&apos;s / sister</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Recent statutes, however, now allow a man to marry his deceased wife&apos;s sister or his deceased brother&apos;s widow. He cannot however marry his <mark>divorced wife&apos;s sister</mark> during the lifetime of his former wife or his brother&apos;s divorced wife during the lifetime of his brother. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 18</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
